  "prompt": "What was a victorian gentleman?",
  "response": "A Victorian gentleman was a man from the middle or upper class during the reign of Queen Victoria (1837-1901) who adhered to a strict code of conduct and social standards. Key characteristics included:\n\n1. Social Status\n- Typically from wealthy or educated backgrounds\n- Belonged to the middle or upper class\n- Often had professional careers or inherited wealth\n\n2. Moral Characteristics\n- Emphasized personal honor and integrity\n- Practiced strict moral and ethical standards\n- Valued politeness, refinement, and self-discipline\n\n3. Behavior and Etiquette\n- Demonstrated impeccable manners\n- Dressed formally and conservatively\n- Followed complex social rules and protocols\n- Practiced chivalry towards women\n- Maintained emotional restraint\n\n4. Education\n- Well-educated, often through private tutoring or prestigious schools\n- Knowledgeable in literature, arts, and sciences\n- Spoke multiple languages\n- Valued intellectual pursuits\n\n5. Economic Activities\n- Professionals like lawyers, doctors, clergy\n- Businessmen, merchants, or landowners\n- Often involved in colonial administrative roles\n\n6. Social Expectations\n- Expected to provide for and protect their family\n- Represented respectability and social standing\n- Participated in civic and philanthropic activities\n\nThe Victorian gentleman embodied the idealized male persona of the era's social expectations.",
